# Backend Patterns

## Layer flow (strict)

routes → [authenticate | validate] → controller → service → model

- Controllers: parse req, call service, `res.json(ok(...))` — no DB, no business logic
- Services: business logic, `throw new AppError(status, msg)` — no req/res
- Routes: path + method + middleware only

## Imports & naming

- Use `@/path/file.js` (ESM requires `.js` extension)
- Files: kebab-case · Exports: camelCase · Classes: PascalCase

## Responses & errors

- JSON APIs: `ok(data)` / `fail(message, code?)` from `@/utils/envelope.js`
- Expected failures: throw `AppError` in service — import from `@/errors/app-error.js`; never manual `res.status` in service
- Async controllers: wrap with `asyncHandler`

## Adding a feature

1. validator → service → controller → route
2. Register route in `routes/index.ts`
3. Mount in `app.ts`: `app.use("/api/v1", apiRoutes)`

## Do not

- Put logic in wrong layer
- Commit `.env` or add unrelated dependencies
